{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. The jetbridge is connected to the plane. Open the aircraft door.",
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Open the aircraft door.",
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        model_name = "gpt-5.4-mini"  # “gemini-3.1-pro" "gemma4:12b-mlx" "qwen3:8b" "claude-haiku-4-5" "claude-sonnet-4-6"  
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "aircraft_door_opening_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
 I am in charge of opening the door of the aircraft at the gate. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },       
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connect."
                        },  
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of stairtruck connection."
                        },
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type (jetway or stairtruck)."
                        },
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "ACU connection status. Required when internally calling stairtruck_connect."
                        },
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "GPU connection status. Required when internally calling stairtruck_connect."
                        },
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Wheelchocks installation status."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","gate_id","flight_status"] 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of opening the aircraft door at the gate.

CRITICAL: You are a sequential executor. Execute every step below in
order. Do NOT return until you reach RETURN SUMMARY.

STEP 1 — Resolve prerequisites
  Call TrackerAPI with flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status,
  gate_id, jetbridge_connection_status, stairtruck_connection_status,
  deplaning_equipment_type.
  Wait. Read back all values.

STEP 2 — Verify flight status
  flight_status must contain 'on blocks' or 'block'.
  If not, stop and report: "Aircraft is not yet on blocks.
  Door cannot be opened."

STEP 3 — Ensure deplaning equipment is connected (ONE call if needed)
  Check deplaning_equipment_type:
    - If deplaning_equipment_type contains 'jetway' or 'jetbridge':
        Required: jetbridge_connection_status contains 'connected'.
        If not connected: call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_jetbridge_connect.
        Wait. Store jetbridge_connection_status via TrackerAPI.
        If still not connected, stop and report failure.
    - If deplaning_equipment_type contains 'stairtruck' or 'stair':
        Required: stairtruck_connection_status contains 'connected'.
        If not connected: call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_stairtruck_connect
        with named parameters:
          flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
          acu_connection_status, gpu_connection_status,
          wheels_chocks_installation_status.
        CRITICAL: acu_connection_status and gpu_connection_status MUST be
        passed explicitly — stairtruck_operator requires both to be
        'connected' to proceed. Do NOT omit them.
        Wait. Store stairtruck_connection_status via TrackerAPI.
        If still not connected, stop and report failure.
    - If deplaning_equipment_type is unknown:
        Accept either jetbridge_connection_status='connected'
        OR stairtruck_connection_status='connected' as sufficient.
        If neither is connected, call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_jetbridge_connect
        as default. Wait. Store result via TrackerAPI.

STEP 4 — Open the door
  Before calling door_operator, confirm the correct equipment is connected:
    - If deplaning_equipment_type contains 'jetway' or 'jetbridge':
        Confirm jetbridge_connection_status='connected' (verified in STEP 3).
        Pass jetbridge_connection_status='connected' to door_operator.
    - If deplaning_equipment_type contains 'stairtruck' or 'stair':
        Confirm stairtruck_connection_status='connected' (verified in STEP 3).
        Pass stairtruck_connection_status='connected' to door_operator.
        Do NOT pass jetbridge_connection_status — leave it null.
    - If deplaning_equipment_type is unknown:
        Pass whichever connection status is 'connected'.
  If the required connection status is not confirmed as 'connected',
  do NOT proceed — return to STEP 3 to reconnect.
  Call door_operator with named parameters:
    flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
    jetbridge_connection_status, stairtruck_connection_status.
  Wait. Extract door_opening_status from the response.
  Call TrackerAPI to store door_opening_status.

RETURN SUMMARY:
  ************************************
  * Summary of aircraft door opening *
  ************************************
  ** flight status                   **: [flight_status]
  ** deplaning equipment type        **: [deplaning_equipment_type]
  ** jetbridge connection status     **: [jetbridge_connection_status]
  ** stairtruck connection status    **: [stairtruck_connection_status]
  ** door opening status             **: [door_opening_status]
            """,

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks.
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "door_opening_status": true
                    }
                },
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true,
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true,
                        "acu_connection_status": true,
                        "gpu_connection_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": true
                    }
                },
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true,
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true,
                        "acu_connection_status": true,
                        "gpu_connection_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": true
                    }
                },
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true,
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["TrackerAPI","door_operator","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_jetbridge_connect","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_stairtruck_connect"]
        },

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check the status of the jetbridge connection to the aircraft. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "ground_services_request_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the inquiry received for grand services."
                        },         
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu readiness status."
                        },     
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the acu connection status."
                        },     
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu connection status."
                        },     
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connect."
                        },   
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the stairtruck connection status."
                        },
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type (jetway or stairtruck)."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_door_opening.aircraft_door_opening.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 

        {
            "name": "door_operator",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent opens the door of the aircraft. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },     
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connect. Null on stairtruck gates."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This is the status of stairtruck connection. Null on jetway gates."
                        },
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },  
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","gate_id"] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_door_opening.aircraft_door_opening.door_operator" 
        }, 
    ],
}
